/etc/network/interfaces

@ if you want use pppoe, install pppoe and pppoeconf, then run pppoeconf as root

@ restart network:
 	  /etc/init.d/networking restart

@ use wireless
 for wireless see : https://wiki.debian.org/WiFi#Configure_Interface
      	       	     https://wiki.debian.org/WiFi/HowToUse
 see the example file interfaces.wireless

 install the wireless driver firstly,in my pc, it's to download the
 brcm43225 driver, install it by run :
	dpkg -i firmware*_all.deb
 install wireless-tools and wpasupplicant
